A multiplicative utility model for responder behavior, incorporating fairness and absolute monetary amount. Fairness is calculated as the ratio of the participant's received proportion to their expected proportion based on token contributions. The model has two learnable parameters: fairness_sensitivity and absolute_amount_weight.  The utility of accepting an offer is the product of the fairness-scaled proportion of money received and the absolute amount of money.
